name: Hanging Out For Any Assasination Now
description:
An eBook of words & images.

All words & images by Shane Jesse Christmass.

EXCERPT:

"Burglars and garrotters muttering threats and curses. 

"Bring out your doctors! Bring out your help!”

Compared to this. The betting ring. The start of the next race. The next day after the race. Morning. The sunset gun booms. Looking back toward the bridge. Everyone’s face complains. Impotent struggles. Nothing else is interesting. Thrash metal soothes. G-Funk as well. Hearts. Lost. Morning. Streamlets. Seas. Bubblegum breath. Vomit. Clouds. The rioting mobs have a meeting in the street. A fight breaks out. The mob takes possession of a government building. They steel themselves in for a firelight. The evening sheds a brilliant glow. Young surgeons operate in basements. General Pixy succeeds General Wool and neither of them knows how to quell this insurrection. Vomit. The tiniest, solitary things. Cherry gets consumed in a military draft. Conscription of woman soldiers. The men hide under the bed blanket..."

name: Towers of Skulls Proportion in the Lap of Chaos
description:
An eBook about the turnpike where an evangelist found the nuzzler of gangland.

Words / Images by Shane Jesse Christmass.

EXCERPT:

"The unicycle animator functions in an original drop. Flashcube going off. Irrigators on the plantation. The apartment where I had been following an impulsive, sudden and unexpected thought. The two boys reached Bobbie first. They subsequently became the scorn of this community. Suffolk County District Attorney described it as the most egregious case in a wave of U.S. murders. A June holdup at Haven Drugs in Medford. Heartbreak: Mary Moran, seen here clutching a photo of her within that situation. Litigants in the courts. I told Frank I was going to bring him promise, in some way, or else. The Cabdrivers hiss, they gnash their teeth. Interviews, cross-examination conducted under the late afternoon sun. Bobbie sitting to my right. She might teach us how to be easeful in the light. Collective farmlands. Six thousand years of history, of misery, of wormwood. We are shadows of the massy temples. How’d you get in. You gave me the keys. Clouds of ether. Mouth wide open in fright. Frank shows me the door. A mass of hanging bodies..."

name: Roman Perth
description:
An eBook about the hibernating brushlike sonnets of fetiches.

OR: a hate-product to my hometown.

Words by Shane Jesse Christmass.
Images by WAN. 

EXCERPT:

"“Not that, the insect spray”

Al picked up the spray. He handed it to Waller.

Waller pulled a plastic bag from his back pocket. He opened the zip lock, picked up the spray, sprayed a heavy amount into the bag, furiously zipping the lock again. 

Waller shook the bag, making the buds, the insect repellent, the wet residue all mix.

“You ever smoked lacey?” Waller said..."

name: 666 Should Become The Sea
description:
A poem about the conductor of transgender sand-soaps. 

EXCERPT:

"666 should become the sea and meet marine-flowed falsity
     the lurid catch of the trawling force
     the swell, the hairy-tailed current of the towering ocean-drift
     the inflected forms of this Neptune-temple adorned
     the fermenting dearth of the river-crow
     the watery pastoral of cocaine and paint fumes
     a coronial of limp coastline and imperialism
     a brooming dock of flying fish and dervish wind"
